-- Angola Plans to Establish Fund to Pay for Infrastructure, Nacional Says
-- Candido Mendes
-- 2010-08-02T07:31:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/angola-plans-to-establish-fund-to-pay-for-infrastructure-nacional-says.html

          
          
             Angola plans to reserve earnings from
oil production of 100,000 barrels per day to form a fund to pay
for infrastructure including power supply and water provision
projects, Luanda-based Radio Nacional de Angola said, citing the
government.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
